1. Fallow instractions on this page

   https://docs.ros.org/en/jazzy/Installation/Ubuntu-Install-Debs.html

2. Setup environment

   $ sudo apt install gedit
   $ gedit .bashrc
  save this line in opened page 
  source /opt/ros/jazzy/setup.bash

3. RUN first ROS2 program for validation that ROS2 is working
  in a terminal run this command
   $ ros2 run demo_nodes_cpp talker
  you have to see Hello World
  in another terminal run 
   $ ros2 run demo_nodes_cpp listener
  you MUST see I heard: [Hello World: number]
  otherwise your ROS2 is not working properly
   ctrl+c